article.headline: Air Force 75, Colorado Christian 61
article.story: AIR FORCE ACADEMY, Colo. (AP) -- Anwar Johnson, Tim Anderson and Andrew Henke each scored 13 points as Air Force won 75-61 over Colorado Christian of Division II on Saturday. Johnson added five rebounds, and Anderson had five steals for Air Force in its third straight win. Air Force (8-4) jumped out to a 37-17 lead at halftime that proved to be insurmountable. Colorado Christian (5-5) shot 51 percent from the field but was hurt by 29 turnovers. Rory Morgan had 19 points for Colorado Christian, and Brian Stamer had 16 points and 11 rebounds.
